Re: You only have to become stronger than your opponent
by spin13 » Fri 02.12.2010 5:48 am Hyperworm wrote:I keep thinking you might be able to do something with さえ (相手より強くさえなれば...??) but it's not quite sounding natural for me...I don't think it works here either. なればいい or なれば十分だ seem good enough.I've never seen an adjective in the ～くさえ～ば form without using ある (あれば). Can anybody confirm whether it is permissible to use other verbs?
You're probably not as smart as you think.Unskilled and Unaware
